OL,6,F"Howard Phillips clearly outlined the
OL,7,Fservices he was willing to provide for
OL,8,Fa hostile state. From gaining
OL,9,Femployment within the civil service
OL,10,Fand applying for security clearance,
OL,11,Fto providing the personal details of
OL,12,Fthe Secretary of State for Defence `
OL,13,FPhillips was brazen in his pursuit for
OL,14,Ffinancial gain and unbothered about
OL,15,Fthe potential detriment to his own
OL,16,Fcountry.
OL,18,F"It is a criminal offence to assist a
OL,19,Fforeign intelligence service,
OL,20,Fregardless of your motive or whether
OL,21,For not you succeed.
